This spontaneous case report (CARE: 0034425540) was received from a father in the UNITED STATES on 14-
JAN-2016 referring to his 5-year-old son who received CHILDREN'S CLARITIN (loratadine) and stated HE MIGHT 
GIVE THIS TO HIS SON TO TREAT A CHRONIC COUGH, SO HE MIGHT TAKE THIS FOR NON-ALLERGY 
RELATED SYMPTOMS. HE MIGHT GIVE HIM 7.5 ML A DAY, and THE DOCTOR RECOMMENDED HE TAKE 
THIS FOR A COUGH.
Product lot number, expiration date and bottle contents were not reported.
